  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The bakery also sold fresh cookies, sweet cakes, and warm milk bread, though Momo only seemed to care about one smell.",
      "zh": "那間麵包店也賣新鮮餅乾、甜蛋糕，還有溫熱的奶油麵包，不過 Momo 好像只在乎一種味道。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The next afternoon, they visited the bakery on the corner, right before 3:33.",
      "zh": "隔天下午，他們在三點三十三分之前去了轉角那間麵包店。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The smell hit them before they even opened the door: warm bread, fresh and sweet.",
      "zh": "他們還沒開門，那股味道就先撲鼻而來：溫熱的麵包，新鮮又香甜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Every day at this time,\" the woman working there said, \"we finish baking the bread.\"",
      "zh": "「每天這個時間，」在裡面工作的女士說：「我們剛好烤好麵包。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"And the smell goes... where, exactly?\" Coco asked.",
      "zh": "Coco 問：「那味道會飄去⋯⋯哪裡呢？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The woman smiled. \"Right out that window, and straight down the street, if the wind is right.\"",
      "zh": "女士笑了：「就從那扇窗戶飄出去，如果風向對的話，會一路飄到街上。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice looked at Coco. \"Momo doesn't hear anything at 3:33,\" she said. \"She smells something.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 看著 Coco：「Momo 三點三十三分不是聽到什麼，」她說：「她是聞到了什麼。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They walked back to school just in time to watch Momo stand, face the gate, and bark, right on schedule.",
      "zh": "他們走回學校，剛好趕上看 Momo 站起來，面向校門，準時開叫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not a mystery,\" Coco said, laughing. \"It's just a very good sense of smell.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 笑著說：「這根本不是謎團，只是嗅覺特別靈敏而已。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The guard admitted he had never once thought to check what was across the street.",
      "zh": "警衛承認他從來沒想過要去看看街對面有什麼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Fourteen years working here,\" he said, \"and I never noticed the bakery finished baking at exactly the same time every day.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「我在這裡工作十四年了，卻從來沒注意到那間麵包店每天都在一樣的時間烤好麵包。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The new episode was short and mostly funny, ending with Bernice eating a piece of bread on air.",
      "zh": "這一集又短又好笑，結尾是 Bernice 在錄音時邊講邊吃著一片麵包。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Some cases,\" she said, mouth full, \"really do end at a bakery.\"",
      "zh": "她嘴裡塞滿食物說：「有些案子，真的會在麵包店結束。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That night, Coco looked at their growing list of cases and noticed something for the first time.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，Coco 看著他們越來越長的案件清單，第一次注意到一件事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Six cases. Six very different answers. But the Friday Box itself had never once been part of the story.",
      "zh": "六個案子，六種非常不同的答案，但 Friday Box 這個箱子本身，卻從來沒有真正成為故事的一部分。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Who even started the Friday Box?\" she asked Bernice suddenly. \"Was it always Mr. Pan's idea?\"",
      "zh": "她突然問 Bernice：「Friday Box 到底是誰開始的？一直都是潘老師的主意嗎？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice thought about it. \"I actually don't know,\" she said. \"We never asked.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 想了想：「我其實不知道，」她說：「我們從來沒問過。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "For the first time since they started the podcast, they realized there was one case they had never opened: their own.",
      "zh": "從他們開始做這個 podcast 以來，他們第一次意識到有一個案子，他們自己從來沒有打開過：就是他們自己的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The bakery owner said running a small business meant waking up before sunrise almost every single day.",
      "zh": "麵包店老闆說，經營一間小生意代表幾乎每天都得在日出前起床。"
    }
  ],
